    "name": "Camille (3)",
    "profile": "Camille was probably the most widely known alter ego of Prince's, and has been credited on the \"Sign O' The Times\" album, which contained some songs from an unreleased [url=http://www.discogs.com/Camille-Camille/release/7273660]Camille album[/url]. This unreleased album was merged with the also unreleased Revolution album \"[m=698798]\" to create a 3-disc album called \"[r=6720328]\" (unrelated to the [url=http://www.discogs.com/Artist-Formerly-Known-As-Prince-Crystal-Ball/master/355175]1998 album[/url] of the same name), also planned to be credited to Camille. At the insistence of Warner Bros., this was condensed into the 2-disc \"Sign O' The Times\", which was released as a Prince album, with Camille credited for vocals on some tracks.\r\nCamille is characterised by the sped up vocals used on the tracks.",
